                "imgDesc": "<p>Sometimes, there will be a beam receptor mirror and an associated <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">beam projector mirror</span> on a lifting column. When a beam shines on the receptor mirror, it will be emitted from the <span style=\"color: #FFE14B\">convex</span> projector mirror.</p>",
                "key": "Page 1/2"
              },
              {
                "img": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/01/14/94376896/4e599c109c172e67b983646791a7ed89_7644247597711261578.png",
                "imgDesc": "<p>Sometimes, lifting columns will have spherical beam relays. When they receive a beam, they will transfer it to the associated beam generator, which will project a beam outward. Receiver nodes can control the direction of the beam generator.</p>",
                "key": "Page 2/2"
